hey i'm working on a shopify theme and the product page looks broken on mobile. the product image is overlapping the title and price on iphone screens. i think it's a margin issue but i cant figure out which line is killing it. here is the css for the product media section:

.product__media-wrapper {
  position: relative;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.product__media-item {
  margin-left: -15px;
  width: 100%;
}

.product__info-container {
  padding: 0 15px;
}

any idea why that negative margin is messing everything up on smaller screens?

